  },
  {
    question: "How does Astroship compare to other similar services?",
    answer:
      "Astroship's API platform is a highly reliable and feature-rich service that offers a wide range of tools and functionality. It is competitively priced and offers a variety of billing options to suit different needs and budgets.",
  },
];
---

<Container>
  <Sectionhead>
    <Fragment slot="title">2024 Official Tournament Rules</Fragment>
    <Fragment slot="desc">Draft. Open for feedback.</Fragment>
  </Sectionhead>

  <div class=" max-w-xl mx-auto mt-8">
    <div class="mt-4 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Tournament Details</h2>
      <div class="flex flex-row">
        <div class="font-bold">Dates:&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>
        <div>Friday, November 1 - Sunday, November 3, 2024</div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-row">
        <div class="font-bold">Format:&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>
        <div>3 rounds of golf (one round per day)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-row">
        <div class="font-bold">Friday, Nov 1:&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>
        <div>Round 1 (3 clubs + putter)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-row">
        <div class="font-bold">Saturday, Nov 2:&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>
        <div>Round 2 (full set of clubs)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-row">
        <div class="font-bold">Sunday, Nov 3:&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>
        <div>Round 3 (full set of clubs)</div>
      </div>
      <br />
      <div class="font-semibold">Award ceremony to follow the conclusion of the final round on Sunday.</div>



      
    </div>
    <div class="mt-4 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Scoring System</h2>
      <div>1. Modified Stableford scoring will be used for each round.</div>
      <div>2. The player with the most points at the end of the three rounds will be declared the winner.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-4 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Handicap</h2>
        <div>50% of each player's handicap will be applied.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-4 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Equipment Rules</h2>
      <div class="flex flex-row">
        <div class="font-bold">Round 1 (Friday, Nov 1):&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>
        <div>Each player is limited to three clubs plus a putter.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-row">
        <div class="font-bold">Round 2 (Saturday, Nov 2):&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>
        <div>Full set of clubs allowed.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-row">
        <div class="font-bold">Round 3 (Sunday, Nov 3):&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>
        <div>Full set of clubs allowed.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-4 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Modified Stableford Scoring</h2>
      <div>Double Eagle: 8 points</div>
      <div>Eagle: 5 points</div>
      <div>Birdie: 2 points</div>
      <div>Par: 1 point</div>
      <div>Bogey: 0 points</div>
      <div>Double Bogey or more: -2 points</div>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-4 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Tiebreaker</h2>
      <div>In the event of a tie for first place after three rounds, a putting competition will be held immediately following the final round to determine the winner.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-4 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Additional Rules</h2>
      <div>1. All other standard golf rules apply as per the R&A and USGA.</div>
      <div>2. Players must record their scores after each hole and submit via the mobile phone app (TBD). This allows for a live leaderboard throughout the event. Paper scorecards must be attested, signed, and turned in at the end of each round.</div>
      <div>3. Any disputes will be resolved by the tournament committee, whose decision will be final.</div>
    </div>

    </div>







  </div>
</Container>
